# Polylog6 Cursor Rules

## Project Structure
- Keep only actionable code
- Remove redundant documentation
- Organize scripts by purpose
- Maintain clean project structure

## Code Standards
- Python: PEP 8, type hints, ruff linting
- TypeScript: Strict mode, ESLint
- Rust: rustfmt conventions

## Development Workflow
- Use unified_launcher.py for development
- Run tests before committing
- Use conventional commits
- Keep GitHub Actions workflows updated

## File Organization
- Source code in src/
- Tests in tests/
- Scripts in scripts/
- Essential docs in docs/
- Remove redundant summaries and status files

## Testing
- Write tests for all new features
- Run tests before committing
- Use GitHub Actions for CI/CD

## Documentation
- Keep only essential architecture docs
- Remove redundant status/summary files
- Consolidate related documentation
- Update README.md for quick reference
